<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     ACT III (cont.) · Chapters 4 & 5
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="sp2-story sp2-story--continued">
  <div class="sp2-story-inner">
    <!-- Chapter 04 -->
    <article class="sp2-chapter">
      <div class="sp2-chapter-index">
        <span class="sp2-chapter-num">04</span>
        <span class="sp2-chapter-date">2024 · Target Culture Mapping</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sp2-chapter-body">
        <h3>Workshops captured, visualized, shared — in real time.</h3>
        <p>Target Culture Mapping is the workshop tool — used in <strong>over eighty executive workshops</strong> to help leadership teams align on the culture they want to build. The old version was a whiteboard and a PowerPoint deck the consultant wrote up afterwards. The redesigned version let the facilitator capture decisions as they happened, visualize the target culture against the current one live, and share the output with the room before everyone left.</p>
        <p>The experience shifted from "we'll send you the summary next week" to "you're leaving this room with your target culture on a page."</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Chapter 05 -->
    <article class="sp2-chapter">
      <div class="sp2-chapter-index">
        <span class="sp2-chapter-num">05</span>
        <span class="sp2-chapter-date">2024 · The acquisition</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sp2-chapter-body">
        <h3>Walking the Talk, acquired by ZRG Partners.</h3>
        <p>Six tools in, the firm was no longer a boutique consulting practice with software on the side — it was a methodology-backed product business. <strong>ZRG Partners acquired Walking the Talk</strong>, folding the firm's culture practice into its global executive-search and leadership-advisory business.</p>
        <p>The redesigned software wasn't the whole reason for the acquisition, but it was a material one. Fortune 500 self-service had made the practice buyable.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     ACT IV · THE SHIFT — service-model redesign
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="sp2-service">
  <div class="sp2-service-inner">
    <div class="sp2-service-head">
      <p class="sp2-service-eyebrow">Service redesign</p>
      <h2>The Shift.</h2>
      <p class="sp2-service-lede"><strong>The tool is the product. But the service model is the business.</strong> Two places where the redesign changed how the firm operates.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="sp2-service-cases">
      <div class="sp2-service-case">
        <span class="sp2-service-case-tag">01 · Portal self-serve</span>
        <h3 class="sp2-service-case-title">Days of waiting collapsed into minutes.</h3>
        <div class="sp2-service-case-body">
          <p>Culture Insights Survey used to require a consultant to compile the data, author an interpretation, and walk the client through it — usually on a call days or weeks after the survey closed. The redesigned portal gave HR leaders and executives instant results, visualized in the firm's methodology, and designed to be read without an expert on the line.</p>
          <p>Consultants still came in — but for interpretation and intervention, not for summary. The firm's senior time moved up the value chain.</p>
          <div class="sp2-service-case-metric">
            <span class="num">Days → Minutes</span>
            <span class="label">Time to insight · Culture Insights Survey portal</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sp2-service-case">
        <span class="sp2-service-case-tag">02 · Workshop capture</span>
        <h3 class="sp2-service-case-title">The summary left the room with the team.</h3>
        <div class="sp2-service-case-body">
          <p>Target Culture Mapping took executive workshops from "we'll send the deck next week" to live capture: the facilitator maps the target culture as the team talks, the visualization updates in real time, and the output is shareable before anyone leaves the room. Eighty-plus workshops have run on the redesigned tool.</p>
          <p>It changed how leadership teams engaged with their own output — the artifact wasn't a deliverable, it was the meeting.</p>
          <div class="sp2-service-case-metric">
            <span class="num">80+</span>
            <span class="label">Executive workshops run · Target Culture Mapping</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

